'''Obor''', the Hill Titan, is the hill [[Giant (race)|giant]] [[boss]] residing in his lair, located behind the locked gates found at the western wall of the hill giant area in the [[Edgeville Dungeon]].

A [[giant key]] is needed to unlock the [[Gate (Obor)|gate]] leading to Obor's lair for the first time, which may be acquired by killing [[Hill Giants]]. Subsequent access to the lair does not require a key. The key will not be consumed when unlocking Obor's lair. When the player first enters Obor's lair, they will be in a safe zone, where they must climb down the rocks in order to fight him. Obor attacks with [[Melee]] and [[Ranged]].

After defeating Obor, the [[Chest_(Obor's_lair)|chest]] present in his lair can be opened for loot by consuming the [[giant key]], similarly to [[Bryophyta]].

Obor can be fought repeatedly by attempting to open [[Chest (Obor's Lair)|his chest]]. This will trigger him to respawn shortly after, regardless of whether the player has a [[giant key]] in their inventory. This means you can continue to kill him as a method of obtaining more keys, which he drops at a rate of 1/16. However, using the key on the chest is required for the [[kill count]] to increase and to obtain the loot from the chest after the fight.

Obor will also respawn immediately upon leaving and re-entering the instance. When changing worlds while in the instanced zone, the player will be teleported outside the instance.

Obor's ranged attack deals 50% less damage when [[Protect from Missiles]] is used.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1354043801187319809|date=26 January 2021|archiveurl=https://reldo.runescape.wiki/i/104955|archivedate=2 March 2021|quote=It has a ranged attack that deals 50% less damage if you've got that prayer active. That sounds intentional to me - we do this sort of damage reduction quite often with bosses.}}

